488e0bf6-55e4-4527-9c38-bbf7c561bc9b	7e19f76d-5971-41ff-96cf-6dbebb85ae9d	242. Valid Anagram	valid-anagram	## [242. Valid Anagram](https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-anagram)\n\n### Description\nGiven two strings `s` and `t`, return `true` if `t` is an `anagram` of `s`, and `false` otherwise.\n\n**Example 1**\n```\nInput: s = "anagram", t = "nagaram"\nOutput: true\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n```\nInput: s = "rat", t = "car"\nOutput: false\n```\n\n## 1. Hash Map Approach (Optimal)\nIf the input constraints were removed (e.g., containing symbols, uppercase letters), `unordered_map` becomes the most intuitive and robust solution.\n\n```cpp\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {\n        if (s.size() != t.size())\n            return false;\n\n        unordered_map<char, int> umap;\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {\n            umap[s[i]]++;\n        }\n\n        for (int j = 0; j < t.size(); j++) {\n            umap[t[j]]--;\n            \n            if (umap[t[j]] < 0) {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n\n        return true;\n    }\n};\n```\n\nComplexity Analysis\n- Time Complexity: $O(n)$\n    - We iterate through the string once.\n- Space Complexity: $O(1)$ / $O(k)$\n    - For English letters, map size is max 26 ($O(1)$).\n    - For general Unicode, size is proportional to unique characters ($O(k)$).	f	[]	2026-01-24 17:03:03.97	3
